description.narrative: (West Bank and Gaza): The Local Government and Infrastructure Program (LGI) is a program that aims to improve local governance and provide the basic infrastructure necessary for sustainable improvements in the quality of life for Palestinians. The program will strengthen local government capacity to respond effectively and efficiently to community needs by supporting capacity building, institutional development and service delivery skill enhancement initiatives. Governance activities will include promoting and institutionalizing good governance practices; encouraging public involvement through participatory governance mechanisms; and enhancing the capacity of the Ministry of Local Government to assume regulatory, policy development and strategic planning responsibilities. Over the life of the program, nearly 147 infrastructure projects will be completed under LGI to benefit over half a million Palestinians. In FY 2014, LGI will direct $15.98 million out of FY 2014 ESF to support the Palestinian Authority's High Impact Micro-Infrastructure Initiative (HIMII). HIMII projects will create jobs and fund infrastructure projects throughout the West Bank including the construction and repair of health clinics, roads, water systems, community centers, and schools. The HIMII is designed to show tangible benefits to the lives of Palestinians as peace negotiations advance and lay the groundwork for further economic growth. In addition, LGI will provide $3.5 million out of FY 2014 ESF funds in support of HIMII to strengthen the institutional and service delivery capacities of local governments; develop and institutionalize tools for citizen engagement in governance processes; strengthen local government capacity to respond to community infrastructure needs and manage sustainable government projects; and support national policy and regulatory reforms for the local governance sector. This program partially contributes to the Agency's education earmark.
